WorkItem.ClosedComment: 1) You shouldn't be loading low level characters into Rawr, it's for 85s and all the rotations and logic in the program is set up for 85s. It won't even be close to right for a level 272) The optimizer's nature will sometimes result in a lower score than what you started with. It happens and a -0.34% change is nothing to worry about (for a level 85, properly equipped character)
WorkItem.Description: Running Raw 4.2.4 on a 27th lvl Druid, the optimiser said I should take off some kit, resulting in a -ve change.

Comments.Message: Here's the output from wow to feed into rawr
Rawr is not designed for anything other than maximum level.  If you are using it for characters less than level 85, we cannot help you.
